// SPEC §6.13 — `<name throttled=Nms> = expr` is the canonical state-decl
// reactivity attribute form for throttled reactive state, parallel to
// `debounced=`. The pre-v0.next `@throttled name = expr` keyword-form was
// retired at S79.
//
// Throttle semantics: the first write in any quiescent window emits
// immediately; subsequent writes within DURATION are suppressed but the
// most recent value is held; at window-end one trailing fire emits with
// the held value. (Standard leading+trailing throttle.)
<scrollY throttled=100ms> = 0
<p>${@scrollY}</>
